re-based discovery, and automated reasoning. Evaluation will be conducted on a newly annotated corpus of PubMed abstracts aligned with both AMR structures and UMLS annotations. We expect significant improvements over baseline AMR parsers and existing knowledge-enhanced NLP models in terms of SMATCH score, entity F1, and relation correctness, particularly for rare and ambiguous entities. The resulting system will provide a foundation for explainable AI in biomedicine, enabling traceable connections between text-derived meaning and established biological knowledge.",
